Are you looking for an opportunity to apply your skills and talent to spark both innovation and positive social change? Symend is a rapidly growing fintech company that combines behavioral science with advanced AI, data, and analytics capabilities to enable companies to engage at-risk customers more effectively and humanely. By creating better ways to approach individuals with empathy and dignity at the time when they need it most, Symend’s employees are helping to transform the debt recovery industry and improve lives in North America and around the world.

The Opportunity

This person will manage the people, processes and technology for the backend of an analytics platform and its data models that empower the company to be data-driven. This role is critical to empowering self-serve analytics and increasing the data maturity level across the organization.
What You'll Be Doing:
Provide people leadership to the team, ensuring they feel heard and respected but also ensuring they receive the feedback necessary for personal growth and to remain strong contributors to Symend;
Establish and maintain a strong, agile, sprint-based SDLC and QA process that aligns with the rest of the engineering teams;
Establish and maintain a strong git-based code management workflow that aligns with the rest of the engineering teams;
Build strategies to gather more data into the system and empower more teams to access and analyze the data;
Build processes to measure and hold the team accountable to a high level of data quality and data integrity;
Build processes to measure and hold the team accountable to a high coverage of unit testing across the codebase;
Build processes (including communication, change management and expectations management) for incidents, defects and bugs that crop up, impacting teams dependent on the data;
Establish a documentation scheme (data dictionary, catalog, lineage) that enables democratization of the data;
Establish and maintain a training program that explains the datasets that are available;
Establish an intake process for building / transforming new or adjusted datasets that are prototyped by the various Data services teams (Data Science Services, Analysis Services);
What You'll Need:
Proven experience as the product owner of an analytics platform;
Proven experience as a leader on data projects which require strong collaboration across multiple stakeholders;
Proven experience as a developer, engineer, architect or combination thereof;
Experience with modern analytical systems and reporting structures;
Strong people management skills, as well as experience mentoring teams and senior engineers to high performance
Experience presenting in front of executives or boards
BSc/BA in computer science or a relevant field

Key Competencies and Skills:
Technical expertise in Business Intelligence or Enterprise Analytics
A critical eye for data and the information that can be uncovered from it
An analytical mindset with problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
All positions require background screening. This will include criminal and education checks to comply with regulations.

Why Symend?
We could tell you all about our competitive compensation, flexible work environment, beer Fridays, and
awesome team events, but working at Symend is so much more than that!
Working at Symend means being part of a driven and collaborative team that values trust, accountability and continuous learning. We work hard, but always make time for fun!
You get the chance to do work that matters on a product that truly changes lives
You get unique opportunities to serve leading global businesses including Tier-1 telecom providers, major utility companies and Fortune 500 financial institutions
You get to make history as we disrupt the debt recovery industry for the good and change the way companies engage with their clients

Ready to do something big?
Send us your resume and tell us why you’d be a fit for Symend.

About Symend
Symend clients achieve exceptional results using state-of-the-art behavioral science and technology to engage at-risk customers with empathy and dignity when they need it most. Symend’s leading software as a service (SaaS) solution and scientifically validated approach empower at-risk customers to resolve past due accounts, while delivering an outstanding customer experience. By proactively engaging customers, Symend’s enterprise clients protect their brands, retain customers, proactively resolve past due accounts and lower their operating costs. Founded in 2016, Symend serves major telecommunications and financial services companies across North America, with plans to expand globally. Symend is headquartered in Calgary and privately held, with offices in Toronto and Denver.
Symend: The science of engagement.™

